&lt;p&gt;The Nuclear Company is the fastest growing startup in the nuclear and energy space, pioneering a fleet-scale approach to building the next generation of nuclear reactors. Through our design-once, build-many model, we&#39;re accelerating the deployment of safe, reliable, and affordable nuclear energy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TNC Services, the services division of The Nuclear Company, supports America&#39;s existing nuclear fleet by delivering specialized maintenance, outage execution, technical expertise, and workforce solutions. Built on the 25-year legacy of Powerhouse Resources, TNC Services combines proven operational expertise with The Nuclear Company&#39;s vision for the future, helping utilities maximize the reliability of today&#39;s nuclear fleet while advancing the next generation of nuclear energy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Account Manager&lt;/strong&gt; is responsible for developing and managing strategic customer relationships within the commercial nuclear power industry. This role serves as the primary point of contact for assigned accounts, partnering with customers to understand their operational goals and maintenance needs while delivering customized service solutions that support plant reliability, outage success, and long-term asset performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working collaboratively with Sales Engineers, Operations, Project Management, Recruiting, and technical service teams, the Account Manager is responsible for driving customer satisfaction, identifying growth opportunities, and ensuring the successful delivery of TNC Services&#39; maintenance, outage, and workforce solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain strong relationships with assigned customer accounts, serving as a trusted advisor and primary point of contact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to expand TNC Services&#39; maintenance, outage, technical, and workforce solutions within existing and prospective accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with customers to understand maintenance strategies, outage schedules, staffing needs, and long-term operational objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Sales Engineers and technical service managers to develop tailored service solutions and proposals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the sales lifecycle from opportunity identification through contract execution and project closeout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare customer presentations, proposals, pricing, and commercial agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain an active sales pipeline and provide accurate forecasting through CRM systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor customer satisfaction and proactively resolve issues to ensure successful project outcomes and long-term partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support contract negotiations while balancing customer expectations and business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Operations and Project Management teams to ensure seamless project execution and effective communication throughout service delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent TNC Services at customer meetings, industry conferences, and networking events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor market trends, customer capital projects, and competitive activity to identify new business opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote a strong culture of safety, quality, integrity, and customer service in all interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualificati

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;The Nuclear Company is the fastest growing startup in the nuclear and energy space creating a never before seen fleet-scale approach to building nuclear reactors. Through its design-once, build-many approach and coalition building across communities, regulators, and financial stakeholders, The Nuclear Company is committed to delivering safe and reliable electricity at the lowest cost, while catalyzing the nuclear industry toward rapid development in America and globally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The Nuclear Company is hiring an AI Engineer 1 to build test automation and quality practices for NOS,&amp;nbsp;the Nuclear Operating System,&amp;nbsp;that&amp;nbsp;meet&amp;nbsp;NQA-1 nuclear quality assurance standards. NOS is the software platform behind one of the largest nuclear buildouts in the United States, and every module it ships must meet the rigor that nuclear regulation demands. This role sits at the intersection of software quality, regulatory compliance, and AI-augmented engineering.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;This is a hands-on, entry-level role with a clear differentiator: you will use AI as a tool to generate, review, and improve tests, while also developing the skills to test AI-powered systems themselves. You will work alongside the Compliance/Quality/Testing Lead, ramp on NQA-1 requirements and Palantir Foundry, and help&amp;nbsp;establish&amp;nbsp;the verification and validation (V&amp;amp;V) practices that give NOS its regulatory backbone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;30&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;hybridMultilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;4&quot; data-aria-level=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Build automated test coverage (unit, integration, and end-to-end) for assigned NOS modules, using AI-assisted generation and review to accelerate coverage and catch gaps.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;30&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;hybridMultilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;5&quot; data-aria-level=&qu

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;The Nuclear Company is the fastest growing startup in the nuclear and energy space creating a never before seen fleet-scale approach to building nuclear reactors. Through its design-once, build-many approach and coalition building across communities, regulators, and financial stakeholders, The Nuclear Company is committed to delivering safe and reliable electricity at the lowest cost, while catalyzing the nuclear industry toward rapid development in America and globally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW106328829 BCX8&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW106328829 BCX8&quot;&gt;The Nuclear Company is hiring an AI Engineer 1 to help build and run the backend, data, and integration layers that NOS depends on. You will report to the Director of Platform Integrations and work in the Platform Integration &amp;amp; AI/Data squad. NOS is the software platform behind one of the largest nuclear buildouts in the United States, and the platform layer is what keeps it fast, reliable, and connected to the systems around it. This is a hands-on, entry-level role. You will work alongside the Platform Engineer and other senior engineers on CI/CD, backend services, and the data and application integrations that tie NOS to internal systems and external sources, taking well-scoped features end to end under senior code review. You will ramp on Palantir Foundry and the team’s AI and data tooling, write production code, open pull requests, and grow into a specialization over time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP Selected SCXW106328829 BCX8&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-parastyle=&quot;heading 3&quot;&gt;First 90 Days:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134245418&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;134245529&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:281,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:281,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;30&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;hybridMultilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;1&quot; data-aria-level=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Help build and&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;the application and data integrations that connect NOS to internal systems, partner APIs, and external data sources, working from well-scoped tickets under senior review.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;The Nuclear Company is the fastest growing startup in the nuclear and energy space creating a never before seen fleet-scale approach to building nuclear reactors. Through its design-once, build-many approach and coalition building across communities, regulators, and financial stakeholders, The Nuclear Company is committed to delivering safe and reliable electricity at the lowest cost, while catalyzing the nuclear industry toward rapid development in America and globally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Nuclear Company is hiring an AI Engineer 1 to join the Product Engineering squad and help ship the NOS modules that field teams, engineers, and operators rely on every day. NOS, the Nuclear Operating System, is the software platform behind one of the largest nuclear buildouts in the United States, and the Product team is responsible for the user-facing experiences that make it real: mobile apps, 3D visualization, digital twin interfaces, and the backend services that power them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on, entry-level role. You will be paired with a senior engineer based on fit and interest, ramp on Palantir Foundry and the team&#39;s tooling, take well-scoped features end to end under senior code review, and grow into a specialization over time, whether that&#39;s mobile, 3D/digital twin, full-stack product engineering, or AI-augmented interfaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pair with senior engineer on a defined NOS module or feature area (mobile, 3D, digital twin, or backend) and learn the codebase, architecture, and review standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take small, well-scoped features end to end, from ticket to pull request to production, under senior code review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help close the NOS module backlog at entry-level scope: bug fixes, UI polish, test coverage, and minor feature additions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ramp on Palantir Foundry, the data ontology, and the AI tooling the team uses to accelerate product development, and start contributing to them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in sprint ceremonies, contribute to technical discussions, and build context on how NOS supports nuclear construction and operations in the field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;Required Experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer science degree or equivalent, with 0-2 years of professional experience (internships, co-ops, and project work count).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong fundamentals in at least one of the following: Python, TypeScript/JavaScript, Swift/Kotlin, C++/C#.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has built something with AI beyond using a chat assistant: multi-step prompts, custom tools, AI features in a codebase, or a small agentic project.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good written and verbal communication, and willingness to learn the nuclear and regulated-industry context.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;The Nuclear Company is the fastest growing startup in the nuclear and energy space creating a never before seen fleet-scale approach to building nuclear reactors. Through its design-once, build-many approach and coalition building across communities, regulators, and financial stakeholders, The Nuclear Company is committed to delivering safe and reliable electricity at the lowest cost, while catalyzing the nuclear industry toward rapid development in America and globally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;The Nuclear Company is hiring an AI Engineer to ship the machine learning and agent capabilities inside NOS, the software platform behind one of the largest nuclear buildouts in the United States.&amp;nbsp;You’ll&amp;nbsp;work in the Platform Integration &amp;amp; AI/Data squad and report to the Director of Platform Integrations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335557856&amp;quot;:16777215,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;This is a hands-on engineering role.&amp;nbsp;You’ll&amp;nbsp;embed ML models and LLM-driven workflows directly into the NOS applications our internal teams and partners use every day: site evaluation, red flag analysis, scheduling, lessons learned, and the stakeholder and project tools that run across active TNC projects.&amp;nbsp;You’ll&amp;nbsp;work close to the metal: training and fine-tuning models, designing agent workflows against NOS data and tools, wiring up MCP interfaces, and standing up the evals and monitoring that keep AI features safe in production.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335557856&amp;quot;:16777215,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;You’ll&amp;nbsp;partner daily with platform engineers, product engineers, and the nuclear domain experts who use what you ship. The team is small, the pace is fast, and the work is visible, what you build will be demoed to utilities, regulators, and financial partners making 20-to-30-year decisions about the future of American nuclear power.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335557856&amp;quot;:16777215,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;Ship ML and AI features inside NOS. Train, fine-tune, and deploy models and LLM-based workflows into production, with the evals, monitoring, and safety controls that make them trustworthy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;Build AI agents and agent workflows. Design agents that operate against NOS data and tools, including the MCP int

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;The Nuclear Company is the fastest growing startup in the nuclear and energy space creating a never before seen fleet-scale approach to building nuclear reactors. Through its design-once, build-many approach and coalition building across communities, regulators, and financial stakeholders, The Nuclear Company is committed to delivering safe and reliable electricity at the lowest cost, while catalyzing the nuclear industry toward rapid development in America and globally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The Nuclear Company is building an AI-tech platform that will deploy America’s next generation of nuclear power plants.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;We have world-class engineers building the AI software: you will&amp;nbsp;use these tools to help our team move fast and execute at the highest level.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;This is a front-row seat&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;one of the most ambitious industrial companies being built in America.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;We are assembling a small cohort of AI Analysts who will work directly within the Office of the CEO to help build an AI-native company from day one.&amp;nbsp;You’ll&amp;nbsp;operate&amp;nbsp;at the intersection of strategy, operations, technology, capital markets, deployment, communications, and execution.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Your job is simple:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Use artificial intelligence to make every person — and every team — around you significantly more productive.&amp;nbsp;For example:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:276}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;One day you may be preparing materials for investors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;The Nuclear Company is the fastest growing startup in the nuclear and energy space creating a never before seen fleet-scale approach to building nuclear reactors. Through its design-once, build-many approach and coalition building across communities, regulators, and financial stakeholders, The Nuclear Company is committed to delivering safe and reliable electricity at the lowest cost, while catalyzing the nuclear industry toward rapid development in America and globally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director, Deployment owns financial planning and analysis for TNC&#39;s active construction portfolio across up to 19 owned nuclear projects, including the Brookfield JV&#39;s anchor project at VCS Units 2 and 3. As developer, TNC contracts EPC firms to build each project; this role tracks capital deployment against the Long-Range Plan and monitors EPC firm performance against contract terms, flagging cost or schedule variances before they hit the P&amp;amp;L. The Director partners directly with Project Directors, the JV finance team, and the VP, FP&amp;amp;A to keep deployment-stage spend disciplined as TNC scales toward IPO. This is a build-it-as-we-grow role: reporting rigor has to scale with a portfolio that adds new projects every quarter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP SCXW174644119 BCX0&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deployment cost tracking. &lt;/strong&gt;Own the monthly actual-vs-budget process for every project in active construction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EPC contractor oversight. &lt;/strong&gt;Monitor draw schedules, change orders, and milestone billing from the EPC firms TNC hires, against contract terms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Variance analysis. &lt;/strong&gt;Identify and explain cost or schedule variances against the LRP for leadership and the board.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Capital deployment reporting. &lt;/strong&gt;Maintain the dashboard tracking capital called, deployed, and remaining by project, mapped to the OWN-[TECH]-[##] project ID convention (TNC’s internal pipeline tracking system).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional partnership.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Work directly with Project Directors, the Brookfield JV finance team, Procurement, and Accounting to keep deployment data clean and current.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;Experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Finance, Accounting, or Engineering, or equivalent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years in FP&amp;amp;A, project finance, or capital/construction finance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct experience managing EPC contracts from the owner/developer side, or overseeing large-scale infrastructure and construction spend.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel and financial modeling skills; able to build variance models from scratch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record managing multi-project or multi-site portfolios under tight reporting deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;

